address: 175 Art center-daero, Yeonsu-gu, Incheon, South Korea
description: G Tower is located in Yeonsu District, Incheon, completed in 2013, near Central Park.

Hongik Park is located near Hongdae. During the Hongik Free Market every weekend, Korean artists and craftsmen sell their creative works here. In the park, wonderful street improv performances are staged at any time, and there is something to stroll and play.

place_name: Hanwha Seoul World Fireworks Festival Site

address: 861-3 Siksa-dong, Ilsandong-gu, Goyang-si, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea

description: The Confucian Temple built by Taizu was destroyed by a fire in 1402 and rebuilt in 1407. After that, it was burnt down again in 1506, and the Imjin Japanese rebellion began in 1601. It was rebuilt almost to its original appearance between 1606 and 1869, and it was overhauled in 1869 to form what it is today. All buildings have their own characteristics, dominated by simple styles and decorative decorations.
